<tr>
<td align=right><tt><b><font size=+2>The 520 Forgotten Bombs:<br>
How U.S. and British Nuclear Weapons<br>
in Europe Undermine the Non-Proliferation Treaty</font></b></tt>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
<b>[Revised and abridged version for the Internet]</b><br>
<font size=-1>An earlier version of this report was released on 18 April, 
1995 for the 1995 NPT Review and Extension Conference. This online version is
presented without the attachments and appendices available <b>only</b> in the 
printed version. To order the printed version, please send $5.00 with a completed copy of the 
<a href="/~usa/pubinfo/order_form.html">USA Public Information order form</a> to our
USA Public Information office.</font>
<p>
<b>Written by Hans M. Kristensen and Joshua Handler</b><br>
<i>Greenpeace International</i><br>
<p>
October 1995
<hr>
<i>About the Authors:</i>
<p><font size=-1>Joshua Handler is Research Coordinator and Hans Kristensen is Senior
Researcher for Greenpeace's Disarmament Campaign in Washington, D.C.
<p>
The authors would like to acknowledge the input and contributions made to this paper by William
M. Arkin, Robert S. Norris of the Natural Resources Defense Council, Stephanie Mills of
Greenpeace International, as well as Otfried Nassauer of the Berlin Information Centre for
Transatlantic Security.</font> 
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<font size=+2><b>Table of Contents</b></font>
<p>
<font size=+1><b><a href="#intro">I. Introduction</a></b></font>
<p> 
