<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>What is Greenpeace?</TITLE>
<META Name="description" Content="Official website for the environmental organization, Greenpeace, in the USA.">
<META Name="keywords" Content="oceans Greenpeace USA environment NGO clean earth water air action protest">
<link rev="made" href:"mailto: jay.townsend@wdc.greenpeace.org">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF FF FF" TEXT="#00 00 80" LINK="#00 80 00" VLINK="#80 00 00" 
ALINK="#FF FF 00">
<center><a href="/~usa/index.html"><img src="pix/whatis1.gif" WIDTH=504 HEIGHT=101 alt="Where is Greenpeace" border=0></a></center>
<p>
<font size=+3><b>Protecting the Oceans</b></font>
<p><IMG ALIGN=right VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10 SRC="pix/trawler2.gif" WIDTH=328
HEIGHT=253 ALT="photo of fishing trawler">
All of us are threatened by those who live for profit only. Overfishing 
and irresponsible fishing practices are destroying fish harvests, damaging 
marine ecosystems, threatening food security, economic stability, and
the livelihoods of tens of millions of people. In fact,
commercial fishing by large factory trawlers is dramatically altering 
species composition in marine ecosystems, endangering marine biodiversity 
and whole populations of fish, marine mammals, seabirds and other 
important predators at the top of the marine food web.
<H3>High-tech floating factories are devastating our seas.</H3>
<P>Short term profits and the spiraling demand for fish products
are driving worldwide over-exploitation of fisheries.  Commerical
operations use trawl nets with openings large enough to encompass
twelve "jumbo jet" aircraft. And gigantic floating factories work
day and night in the last of the planet's great sancuaries,
vacuuming up mountains of fish, leaving ecological devastation in
their wakes.
<H3>Governments offer the world little in hope or vision.</H3>
<P>Governments have failed to stem the tide of overfishing, 
over-investing in vessels and gear, and the uncontrolled expansion of
fishing fleets from depleted fisheries in other regions.
<H3>Control should be placed in the hands of a broader range of
affected groups.</H3>
<P>Decisions concerning fisheries must address the basic issue of
equity -- ensuring that the views and interests of indigenous and
artisanal fishers, fish workers' organizations, environmental
groups and people in affected coastal communities are taken into
account in fisheries development and management.
<P>Greenpeace urges all governments to eliminate overfishing, to
rebuild depleted fish populations, to adopt a precautionary
approach to fisheries management, and to develop more selective
fishing practices to minimize bycatch and waste.
<p>
<b>For more details about factory trawling, see the comprehensive on-line 
Greenpeace report <a href="/~usa/reports/biodiversity/sinking_fast/index.html">"Sinking Fast"</a>.
<p>
<b>For the latest information about this campaign, visit the <a href="/~usa/campaigns/biodiversity/">
USA Biodiversity/Fisheries Campaign page</a>.</b> 
<p>
<hr>
<ul>
<LI><b><A HREF="forests.html">The Fight for the Forests</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="nukes.html">Nuclear Disarmament and Safe
Energy</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="toxics.html">Toxic Poisoning...Environmental
Justice</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="can_do.html">What <I>YOU</I> Can Do</b></LI>
</UL>
<pre>
</pre>
