<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF link=#006400 vlink=#56350D>
<center><img src="pix/headlogo.gif" width="273" height="135" ALT="Eco-Head logo">
<p>
<img src="pix/heading.gif" width="360" height="35">
<p>
<img src="pix/cap.gif" width="201" height="155" ALT="photo of cap">
</center>
<blockquote>
<a href="http://www.eco-heads.com/home.htm">Eco-Heads, Inc.</a> 
introduces our exclusive licensed baseball caps. We use our 100% certified 
organic cotton and add our ecologically-sound low-impact dyes to create colors. 
A portion of proceeds goes to the specific organization of the cap purchased. 
Each cap is $16.95 + $4.95(s/h). Illinois residents pay 8.75% sales tax. Low-profile, 
adult size w/self-adjustable fabric strap. Grown, milled and sewn in America.
<p>
<FONT SIZE=+1>Call <B>1-800-776-3028</B> to order. Major credit cards
welcome.</FONT><br>
<p>
The Greenpeace baseball cap is available in solid natural organic cotton with a 
jade logo. A portion of the proceeds of the sale of each Greenpeace licensed 
organic cotton baseball caps goes to support Greenpeace. Greenpeace, founded 
in 1970, is an independent campaign-focused organization which uses non-violent, 
creative, direct action to expose global environmental problems and to force 
solutions which are essential to a green and peaceful future. Greenpeace is a 
trademark of Greenpeace, Inc.<br>
<p>
</blockquote>
