<HEAD>

<TITLE>Greenpeace Mediterranean: Malta</TITLE>

<BODY BACKGROUND="pics/tile.gif" BGCOLOR=white Text=black link=blue VLINK=purple ALINK=white>

</HEAD>

<!--<FONT SIZE=7><TT><B>Other Countries</B></TT><FONT SIZE=3><BR>-->
<IMG SRC="pics/malta.jpg" ALT="[Malta/Head Office]" ALIGN="absmiddle"><P>

<BR><BR>

The Greenpeace Mediterranean office is located in Malta. Little work has however so far directly concerned Malta itself. Greenpeace ships regularly visit, but these visits are mostly of a logistical nature. This has happened since 1988, long before the Mediterranean office was established in Malta. 
The central position of the island and its neutral democratic standing makes it practical for the co-ordination and preparation of operations.  
The MV Sirius, the SV Rainbow Warrior, the MV Greenpeace, the MV Altair, and now the <A HREF="arcticmalta.html">MV Arctic Sunrise</A> have all visited.
<P>
One issue Greenpeace has recently (1996) taken up in Malta is waste treatment Greenpeace is presently tackling this issue on a regional basis as Mediterranean countries opt for the dangerous Incineration option to their waste problems.  
Malta has not yet decided on adopting this false solution but has given signs of seriously considering this option. 
A Greenpeace report  "The Burning Issue" report about Incinerator projects for the Mediterranean presented includes and analysis of the Maltese situation.
<P>

<BR><BR><BR>

<HR>

<CENTER>

<A HREF="mailto:grnpeace@email.keyworld.net"><IMG SRC="pics/bottle.gif" ALT="[Send us email!]" ALIGN="bottom" BORDER="none"></A>
