<P>Click on blue text in graphic for information about the Brent Spar platform
<P ALIGN=CENTER><a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/brent3">
<img src="brent3.gif" align="bottom" alt="Diagram of Brent Spar" ISMAP></a>
<H4>WHAT IS BRENT SPAR?</H4>
<P>Brent Spar is an old, disused oil installation owned by Shell. It is a cylindrical structure measuring 137 metres in height, which is twice as high as Nelson's Column. 109 meters of the platform is submerged.

<P>The Brent Spar platform was de-comissioned in 1991when it was abandoned and left to rust.
