<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Greenpeace: An Environmental Imperative</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<IMG SRC="PosPaper.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALT="[A Greenpeace International Position Paper" WIDTH="125" HEIGHT="34" BORDER="0">

<IMG SRC="cosmini.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT ALT="[An Environmental Imperative]" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="34" BORDER="0">
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1 FACE="SERIF"><B>
	GREENPEACE POSITION ON METHYL BROMIDE PRODUCTION PHASE OUT
</B></FONT>
</P>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica, Arial">
<P>
	Current phase out schedules are inadequate for the protection of the
ozone layer not only because they allow for unnecessarily prolonged use
of methyl bromide, but also because they fail to curtail continued
production for export once they come into force.
</P>

<P>
	A corresponding production phase out schedule is necessary to remove
incentives for industry to maintain high levels of production for
exports to developing countries.
</P>

<P>
	Furthermore, it is important that companies in industrialized
countries are discouraged through legal and financial measures from
relocating their obsolete methyl bromide production facilities in
developing countries. Such dumping of obsolete technology would
undermine the intent of the Montreal Protocol.
</P>

<P>
	At minimum, countries should require total transparency from
industry in terms of production data in both Article 2 and Article 5
countries.
</P>
</FONT>
<HR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="5phase.html"><IMG HSPACE=3 SRC="../gfx/gpdotbk.gif" ALT="[back]" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="28" BORDER="0">
</A>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../gfx/gpdotup.gif" ALT="[return to index]" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="28" BORDER="0">
</A>
<A HREF="7other.html"><IMG  HSPACE=3  SRC="../gfx/gpdotfd.gif" ALT="[next]" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="28" BORDER="0">
</A></P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
