to US Congress Human Rights caucus):  0
<BR>
<IMG SRC = "icon.gif">        World Bank loans to be committed to the human rights-violating
Indonesian Government in 1994:  $5 billion
<BR>
<IMG SRC = "icon.gif">        In 1992, UK contractors and consultants received $285 million in
fees from the Bank's IDA (International Development Association).
Bangladesh's loan that year from the IDA was $253 million. Bangladesh has
to pay the money back; the UK consultants do not. Switzerland, then not
even a bank member, received more than Sri Lanka and the Philippines.
(source: global exchange).
<BR>
<IMG SRC = "icon.gif">        In 1993, 14 severely indebted countries (mainly African) paid more
in debt services to the World Bank than they received from it in new loans.
<BR>

