</P><P>
Approximately 65 million compressors are produced annually for
domestic refrigerators.<BR>

</P><P>
The three largest manufacturers with over 15 million compressors
annual production:

<UL TYPE=CIRCLE>
	<LI>Matsushita (production mainly in Malaysia): Japanese/Korean

		<LI>Electrolux (Italy, Austria, Spain, US, China, Egypt, India)
		<DD>-Zanusi (Italy)

		<LI>Whirlpool (Embraco / Brasil : production sites in Brasil, Italy, China)
		<DD>-Espera (Italy)
			<DD>-Hermetic Unit (France)
</UL>

</P><P>
Hydrocarbon compressor producers include: 

<UL TYPE=CIRCLE>
 	<LI>European factories of Electrolux, Zanussi, Unidad Hermetica,
	<LI>Verdichter Oe,  Embraco Brazil (Whirlpool), Matsushita

 	<LI>Independent European manufacturers: Danfoss (Denmark), Necchi (Italy), Foron (Germany)

 	<LI>Danfoss is the leadsing manufacturer with 2.5 million sold in 1995

 	<LI>Americold (Electrolux subsidiary): North American isobutane prototype
</UL>

</P><P>
Total global market share for HC compressors is 10%, 40-45% for
HFC-134a</P>
