<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>YEARS OF DROUGHT HAVE DRIED UP BULGARIA'S WATER SUPPLIES
</B></H3><P>

The government is planing cloud seeding in an effort to bring
rain to the region. Virtually all of Sofia's reservoir is dry and
severe water restrictions have been placed on residents.  Water
is supplied 24 hours every three days to the capitals residents
and hot water has been cut off until March. ("Bulgarian capital
may use planes to bring rain",  Reuter, 15 December 1994).<P>

