<H3><B>FLOODS AND HEATWAVES IN BRITAIN </B></H3><P>

Floods have caused massive damage in Glasgow, an estimated UK200
million, and left hundreds homeless. Heavy rains also caused
flooding in Wales and the West and southern counties. Meanwhile
in the south temperatures averaged seven degrees above the
average for late December.  ("Robertson criticise 'patchy'
insurance aid to flood victims", The Herald [Glasgow], 30
December 1994; "Pensioner missing as widespread floods close
roads",  The Times, 28 December 1994).<P>

