<! record 0007 of 844>
<TITLE>SATELLITE SEA LEVEL RESULTS SHOW THE OCEANS ARE
RISING</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>SATELLITE SEA LEVEL RESULTS SHOW THE OCEANS ARE RISING
</B></H3><P>

Over its first two years of operation the Topex/Poseidon
satellite has measures a steady rise in sea level of more than
three millimetres a year. According to Dr. R. Steven Nerem of
NASA, the rate of sea level rise is measured by the satellite's
radar altimeter and "is in reasonable agreement with tide gauge
results." While the participants in the project acknowledge that
two years of data is insufficient to prove the existence of long-
term trends, these observations corroborate the trend in sea
level rise over the last century taken from tide gauges and is
roughly what would be expected from global warming. ("Most
precise gauge yet points to global warming",  New York Times, 20
December 1994).<P>

Note: In 1990 the IPCC reported that sea level rise over this
last century was highly likely and estimated to be around 1-2 mm
per year.<P>

