<TITLE>RECORD WARMTH IN EUROPE IN 1994</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>RECORD WARMTH IN EUROPE IN 1994 </B></H3><P>

Italy experienced its hottest year since 1951, besting its
previous top of 1990. Changes in rainfall have also been reported
in recent times; total rainfall has decreased but extreme events
have increased. Austria had an exceptionally warm  year,
recording temperatures between 1.4 to 2.2 oC above average across
the country and Vienna recorded its most extreme year since 1775.
The Netherlands notched up its third hottest year this century; 
only 1989 and 1990 were warmer and November was the hottest since
1706. Both July and November were record months and July was the
hottest month ever recorded in the Netherlands. The Dutch year
was the fourth wettest recorded, with severe flooding in autumn. 
1994 is expected to be Britain's's sixth warmest this century and
the 8th hottest since 1659. ("Warm year shows evidence of air
pollution", The Independent, 27 December 1994; Corriere della
Sera,  11 December 1994; "Coincidence/chance makes 1994 to a very
warm year", Volkskrant, 1 January 1994; NRC Handelsblad, 31
December 1994; Kurier, 3 January 1994).<P>

