<H3><B>DROUGHT DRIES UP HUNGARY'S SPAS </B></H3><P>

Budapest has been famous for its hot water spas and lidos for
more than two thousand years; up to 20,000 visit every weekend. 
However, the prolonged drought, in combination with over-use, has
contributed to a significant drop in the level of Budapest's
springs and wells. Rainfall in Hungary has been declining for the
past 20 years. ("Hungary's spas in hot water", New Scientist, p.
22-25, 10 December 1994).<P>

