<TITLE>VIRUSES EMERGE AS ENVIRONMENT CHANGES</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>VIRUSES EMERGE AS ENVIRONMENT CHANGES </B></H3><P>

A prominent virologist warns that human modifications to the
environment may result in the emergence of new strains of
viruses, which may cause viral outbreaks costing millions of
lives. Professor Fred Murphy of the University of California says
that deforestation, uncontrolled urban growth, poor irrigation,
expanding agriculture, and modern air travel are assisting the
spread and development of viruses, such as the Ebola virus which
emerged from disturbed tropical rainforest and had a mortality
rate of 88 percent in one outbreak. Insect-borne diseases are a
particular threat. ("Environmental destruction aids emergence of
new killer viruses", The Australian, 30 November 1994).<P>

