<H3><B>MEDITERRANEAN "HEAT WAVES" ARE INCREASING </B></H3><P>

Extended heat waves, defined as 10 days or more,  appear to
becoming more frequent in the Mediterranean.  They are generated
in the area by a sub-tropical configuration of the pressure
system named "omega system", from Morocco-Algeria-Spain to
Turkey. (Corriere Della Sera, [Scientific Supplement], 11
September 1994).<P>

