<! record 0047 of 844>
<TITLE>FEARS OF A "CLIMATE FLIP"</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>FEARS OF A "CLIMATE FLIP" </B></H3><P>

Scientists suggest that even a relatively small increase in
atmospheric levels of carbon dioxide could cause a
disproportionately large effect on climate, or "climate flip".
Professor Wallace Broecher of Lamont Doherty Observatory suggests
that an influx of  fresh water, from melting ice for instance,
could cause the Atlantic Ocean  circulation system to slow down,
halt or switch  direction.  This system is a major engine of the
climate, transporting heat from the southern to the northern
hemisphere.  A halt in the Atlantic circulation would then be
expected to enhance warming in the southern hemisphere,  while
eliminating  or reversing  it in the northern hemisphere. 
Professor John Theide says: "It was a mistake to think that
climate change would be gentle". ("Climatic change could be
abrupt", Daily Telegraph,  13 October 1994).<P>

GREENPEACE Climate Impacts Database<P>

<HR>
Keywords:\CO2\

</BODY>
