<TITLE>POLLEN REVEALS ANCIENT CLIMATE CHANGE</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>POLLEN REVEALS ANCIENT CLIMATE CHANGE </B></H3><P>

The Greenland ice core samples provide conflicting evidence about
the stability or otherwise of the climate in the Eemian period,
prior to the last ice age. Pollen from ancient lake beds and peat
deposits, analysed by Michael Field and colleagues at Cambridge
University,  support the view of an unstable Eemian climate, 
subject to temperature fluctuations. (M.H. Field et al., "Eemian
climate fluctuations observed in a European pollen record",
letter to Nature, v.371, p.779-783, 27 October 1994).<P>

