</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>TEXAS FLOODING WORST IN RECENT MEMORY </B></H3><P>

Heavy rain causes major flooding in parts of Texas, after more
than 70cm falls  over a three day period near Liberty, east of
Houston.  Thirty-three counties are declared disaster areas. The
San Jacinto River breaks its banks; 11,500 people are evacuated
and 18 people drowned. Fuel pipelines in the river explode,
pouring torrents of flame into the floodwaters. The region has
been hit by floods in 1989, 1991 and 1992. The latest downpour
sweeps in on a stalled Gulf of Mexico system. (Associated Press,
22 October 1994; CNN News, 22 October 1994).<P>

