The embattled Brazilian coffee industry is now suffering from
prolonged drought, following shortly after two devastating
frosts. The drought is worse than that of 1985, which wiped out
almost 60 percent of the crop.  The price of coffee on
international commodities markets is fluctuating wildly in
response to  weather reports. (International Press Service, 21
October 1994).<P>

