<TITLE>VEGETATION AND CLIMATE CHANGE</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>VEGETATION AND CLIMATE CHANGE </B></H3><P>

In a letter to Nature, Owen Scholes of Assumption College,
Massachusetts, suggests that previous correspondence predicting
that montane vegetation may have a difficult time coping with
global warming may have underestimated the problem. Scholes
suggests that the prognosis may be worse than feared because
while the effects of temperature rise have been widely
considered, decreases in precipitation have not, and are also
likely.  The range of many species is therefore likely to
contract, as well as to shift. ("Plant survival", Scientific
Correspondence to Nature, v.371, p.66, 20 October 1994).<P>

