<H3><B>CARIBBEAN IN DROUGHT </B></H3><P>

Jamaica, the erstwhile tropical paradise, is in the grip of the
worst drought for 40 years. Banana and coconut crops are
affected, with 916 hectares of bananas ruined since May.  Water
supplies are severely strained; catchment problems being
exacerbated by aggressive  agricultural expansion and
deforestation in recent years. (Interpress Third World News
Agency, 11 October 1994).<P>

