<TITLE>CHINESE FLOOD BILL MOUNTS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>CHINESE FLOOD BILL MOUNTS </B></H3><P>

The economic costs of 1994's frequent flooding episodes are
estimated to have cost China 150 billion yuan. More than 260
million mu of land has been damaged, and 4,300 people left dead
or injured, and losses have exceeded those of the Chang Jiang and
Huai He floods of 1991.  According to Huang Chaozong of the State
Flood-Control and Drought Relief HQ, factors which contributed to
the severity of flooding this year were repeated heavy rainfalls
in some areas, and more frequent typhoons than in other years
(nine, rather than the average of six). (BBC Summary of World
Broadcasts, 6 October 1994).<P>

