<TITLE>THE INDIAN "PLAGUE": WHY NOW?</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>THE INDIAN "PLAGUE": WHY NOW? </B></H3><P>

Recent outbreaks of bubonic and pneumonic plague in India have
emphasised the existence of the reservoir of disease, also
including tuberculosis, hepatitis B, malaria and trypanosome,
which "linger on the margins of human well-being". The "plague"
first appeared in Calcutta, and then in Surat, on the west coast,
prompting an panicked exodus of 300,000 people from Surat.(Sydney
Telegraph Mirror, 29 September 1994).<P>

