<! record 0076 of 844>
<TITLE>EL NINO AND NEW ZEALAND</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>EL NINO AND NEW ZEALAND </B></H3><P>

The effects of El Nino are being felt in New Zealand.  In normal
seasons between El Nino events, easterly and northeasterly winds
predominate, bringing rain to the north and east of the country,
and drier conditions to the west and south.  During El Nino
events such as the current protracted one, drought is common in
the north and east of the country, while the south and west are
likely to experience heavy summer rain.  Until the Southern
Oscillation returns to the La Nina state, this situation is
likely to continue. ("Go south to duck El Nino dry period", New
Zealand Farmer, 28 September 1994).<P>

GREENPEACE Climate Impacts Database<P>

