<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>FLOODING IN RUSSIA </B></H3><P>

Heavy rains causes flooding near Vladivostok, in Russia's far
east, with 5 people dead and 15 missing, and a damage bill
estimated at 700 bn roubles (US$292 m). The worst flooding in the
region for 10 years, it destroys roads, homes and bridges.
Diphtheria has broken out in the city of Nakhodka, and there are
fears of cholera in the region. Further rain is expected.
(Lloyd's Information Casualty Report, 26 September 1994; BBC
Summary of World Broadcasts, 30 September 1994).<P>

