<TITLE>SPRING COMES EARLY IN THE UK</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>SPRING COMES EARLY IN THE UK </B></H3><P>

A report by the Institute of Terrestrial Ecology (ITE) shows that
warm weather between 1988 and 1990 encouraged a northward
movement of  animal and plant species, an early blooming of 
flowers and earlier than usual animal breeding.  Hot summers and
mild winters characterised this period.  Dr Melvin Cannell of the
ITE said that these events were examples of what may happen if
climate change becomes established.(The Scotsman, 24 September
1994).<P>

