<H3><B> HUGE FIRES SMOTHER SOUTHEAST ASIA </B></H3><P>

Huge forest fires in the Indonesian islands of Borneo and Sumatra
have produced thick smoke which is disrupting flights and causing
severe air pollution as far afield as Singapore, where two ships
collided in the poor visibility.  The fires have burnt at least
45,000 hectares of forest, 8,000 of which was natural forest. 
(Reuter, 23 September 1994; Business Times [Malaysia], 24
September 1994; New Scientist, p.10, 15 October 1994).<P>

