<H3><B>HEAT AND POLLUTION STRANGLE ATHENS </B></H3><P>

As pollution reaches drastic levels in Athens' heatwave,
restrictions are placed on private car use in the city area.
Temperatures reach 38oC. Nitrogen dioxide levels reach twice
those recognised as safe, and  many people are hospitalised with
cardiac and respiratory problems. ("Car ban as pollution chokes
Athens", Sydney Morning Herald, 17 September 1994).<P>

