<H3><B>RECORD RAIN DAMAGE IN PAKISTAN </B></H3><P>

The prolonged monsoon season has hindered picking and caused pest
outbreaks in the cotton crop in Sindh province, reducing the
harvest  by about 10 percent. The heavy rains in September prove
to the most damaging in Pakistan's history, leaving 333 people
dead, 4,159 villages affected, 83,000 homes destroyed, 247,000
homes partially destroyed, and over 3,000 cattle lost. (Reuter,
15 September 1994, 19 September 1994, 20 September 1994).<P>

