<TITLE>WARMING THREATENS JAPANESE RICE CROP</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>WARMING THREATENS JAPANESE RICE CROP </B></H3><P>

The Environment Ministry of Japan releases a report detailing
probable effects on Japan of global warming, based on the
International Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) prediction of a 3ƒC
temperature rise by the end of the 21st century. While rice
harvests in cooler northern and eastern Japan will probably
increase as a result of warming, the heat-sensitive Japonica
variety will not thrive in the west and south of the country. The
report also predicts changes in tree distribution, with beech
forests disappearing and being replaced by oak forests. A 10
percent increase in precipitation is also predicted. (Japan
Times, 14 September 1994).<P>

GREENPEACE Climate Impacts Database<P>

