<H3><B>SEVERE FLOODING IN THAILAND </B></H3><P>

Chiang Rai province suffers its worst flooding in 20 years, with
about 80 percent of the province inundated, and 200,000 people
homeless.<P>

Damage estimates range from 100 to 300 million baht, with
thousands of hectares of rice fields damaged. The storm plays
havoc with Thai fishing vessels, sinking two boats and killing
several crew members. (Bangkok Post, 7 September 1994).<P>

