<! record 0101 of 844>
<TITLE>US RESEARCH COUNCIL RECOMMENDS 15 YEAR CLIMATE
STUDY</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG SRC= "../icons/gpclogo.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Logo"><BR>
<H3><B>US RESEARCH COUNCIL RECOMMENDS 15 YEAR CLIMATE STUDY
</B></H3><P>

A National Research Council panel in the US recommends that a 15-
year program be instigated to investigate interactions between
the oceans, land and the air, with a particular focus on the El
Nino effect.  El Nino, characterised by changes in Pacific ocean
water temperatures and air pressure, is thought to have caused
such weather catastrophes as the recent fierce US west coast
storms, heat wave conditions afflicting much of the central
US, the  Australian and Indonesian droughts and the devastation
of South American fisheries.  The proposed research program, to
be known as GOALS - Global Ocean-Atmosphere-Land System aims to
develop computer models of air land and ocean interactions to
reach more accurate forecasts. ("Climate research", Associated
Press, 23 September 1994).<P>

GREENPEACE Climate Impacts Database<P>

